b'     Dear Students,     The Intersection of Engineering and Business: A Masters Program in Technology Entrepreneurship  Date Nov. 7th  Time: 5.30 p.m. to 6.30 p.m.   Venue: Hall#1 IC &SR Building       This talk is led by Sunny;Shah , Assistant Director & Faculty of ESTEEM Graduate Program at the University of Notre Dame. ESTEEMis the first multidisciplinary graduate program at Notre Dame, created in 2009/2010 by the Colleges of Science, Engineering, and Business. ESTEEM is a oneyear graduate program in entrepreneurship and innovation targeted at STEM students and, now in its eighth academic year, is proving to be very successful on many fronts: attracting top students from national and international universities. excellent placement and a distinguishing capstone thesis component.    The ESTEEM programoffers business skills with a focus on entrepreneurship and the commercialization of innovative research and technology.The students gain the knowledge, tools, and techniques required to take an idea all the way from concept to market through a capstone thesis where they work with University research or industry research to develop a comprehensive commercialization plan..    SunnyShahwill talk about his PhD work in Biomedical Engineering and his pivot into a new career of technology commercialization and his current role in ESTEEM where he is incharge of the capstone thesis and thecurriculumdesign. Additionally, he teaches a course in Business Model Canvas and Design Thinking.      Regards   Kavitha                   K avitha G.R (Ms )  Manager    International Relations Office of International Relations l   2 nd Floor, IC & SR Building   I ndian Institute of Technology Madras  l  Chennai    600 036 l  INDIA Tel : (91) 0442257 4926  I  Fax : (91) 0442257 4927  I  Cell : 9444 536574 Email : oir@iitm.ac.in  I Website :    '

